class Solution {
    public int minOrAfterOperations(int[] nums, int k) {
        int ans = 0;
        int mask = 0;
        for (int b = 29; b >= 0; b--) {
            mask |= 1 << b;
            int cnt = 0; // 操作次数
            int and = -1; // -1 的二进制全为 1
            for (int x : nums) {
                and &= x & mask;
                if (and != 0) {
                    cnt++; // 合并 x，操作次数加一
                } else {
                    and = -1; // 准备合并下一段
                }
            }
            if (cnt > k) {
                ans |= mask; // 答案的这个比特位必须是 1
                mask ^= 1 << b; // 后面不考虑这个比特位
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
```

The code uses a bitwise operation to find the minimum possible value of the bitwise OR of the remaining elements of nums after applying at most k operations. The code starts from the most significant bit and checks if it can be set to 1 without exceeding the operation limit k. If it can, it sets the bit to 1 and updates the answer. If it can't, it moves on to the next bit. The code repeats this process until it has checked all bits.

